unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":3},{"ward":"Knutton","seats":1,"turnout_pct":27.36,"results_url":"https://www.newcastle-staffs.gov.uk/downloads/file/3899/knutton","candidates":[{"n":"Graham Paul Shaw","p":"Reform UK","v":359,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128181","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128181/d95eba3a-b5ea-4ef4-8865-418d709d96bf.png"},{"n":"Joshua Gilbert","p":"Labour Party","v":129,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128180","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/128180/5fda98b3-9d6f-4bc4-b0c3-14416548bdc9.png"},{"n":"James Linden Dowler","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":54,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128179"}],"female_count":0,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"Loggerheads","seats":2,"turnout_pct":47.67,"results_url":"https://www.newcastle-staffs.gov.uk/downloads/file/3895/loggerheads","candidates":[{"n":"Graham David Sedgley","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":805,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"125602","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/125602/74b899d6-a627-4ee8-82ed-f59f5b424d97.png","stmt":"Two votes. Real issues. Real results.\nIn the upcoming local elections, you will have TWO votes in the Loggerheads ward. This is a\ngenuine opportunity to make your mark and elect local representatives who will stand up for\nthis community.\nYour Conservative candidates - Graham Sedgley and Andrew Turnock - are committed to\nLoggerheads and understand the issues that matter most to residents here. They are\ncampaigning on the things that directly aﬀect your quality of life:\nStanding up for our rural communities.\nResidents across Loggerheads, Ashley and the surrounding villages are rightly concerned\nabout increasing pressure from speculative housing developments that threaten the character\nof our rural communities. Our candidates will fight for a strong Local Plan that protects our\nvillages from inappropriate development, safeguards our countryside, and ensures that any\nfuture growth is genuinely supported by infrastructure and shaped by local people rather than\nimposed from outside.\nFixing our roads and tackling potholes.\nPoor road conditions and potholes have become a growing frustration for residents and\nmotorists across our area. Roads and pavements are deteriorating and repairs have not\nalways been carried out when they should be. Our candidates will continue pushing\nStaﬀordshire County Council for long-overdue highway improvements, ensuring potholes are\nPromoted by Paul Startin for Staﬀordshire Conservatives and printed by Central Staﬀordshire Conservative\nFederation, both of Castle Street, Staﬀord, ST16 2ED\nrepaired properly and resurfacing programmes are delivered so our roads are safer for\neveryone who relies on them every day.\nProtecting local decision-making.\nMany residents are concerned about proposals that would merge local councils into larger,\nmore remote authorities. Decisions aﬀecting our villages should be made locally by people\nwho understand the area, not by distant bureaucracies. Our candidates will continue to stand\nup for local accountability, protec"},{"n":"Andrew William Turnock","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":730,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"120141","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/120141/37ac9fc6-19a1-4afb-98c6-017d3d0225d3.png"},{"n":"Robert Alwyn Selwood","p":"Reform UK","v":615,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128239"},{"n":"Phillip Arthur Watts","p":"Reform UK","v":532,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128240"},{"n":"Jeff Love","p":"Labour Party","v":274,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"76100","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/76100/d57f96f8-48b3-4a03-969d-9be441eafa18.png"},{"n":"Nigel David John Hadfield","p":"Labour Party","v":242,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128237"},{"n":"Grant Clifford Martin Robertson","p":"Green Party","v":202,"r":7,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128238"}],"female_count":0,"male_count":7,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":2},{"ward":"Madeley & Betley","seats":2,"turnout_pct":43.87,"results_url":"https://www.newcastle-staffs.gov.uk/downloads/file/3901/madeley-betley","candidates":[{"n":"Jill Pamela Whitmore","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":884,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"117920","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/117920/8f1a7416-f7a6-42d1-a5df-10df7e5da474.png"},{"n":"Robert Bettley-Smith","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":832,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"90707"},{"n":"Vicky England","p":"Reform UK","v":549,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128577"},{"n":"Neill Antony Walker","p":"Reform UK","v":533,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"116532","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/116532/ae0d4ef3-4e48-4eeb-a474-1db155bc29f0.png","stmt":"I recently received an email from a local resident living in an Aspire home, expressing significant difficulties in making the changes needed to ensure they can, as Aspire promotes, “Thrive” in their home.\n\nI reached out to Aspire's CEO to raise these concerns, but unfortunately, my correspondence appears to have been ignored. This lack of response speaks volumes about how Aspire is treating its tenants. This is not an isolated incident—this email is one of several I have received. While I am sure many Aspire tenants are satisfied, even one unhappy tenant is one too many.\n\nAs some of you may know, a new development is underway in Newcastle town center, with the homes being designated as Aspire properties. This raises serious concerns for me, given the apparent struggles Aspire is having with its existing housing stock.  These concerns have motivated me to take action to stand in the upcoming by-election in Town on the 23rd of January. I know it will be a challenging campaign, but I am determined to rally the community and work towards Newcastle-under-Lyme electing its first Reform UK Councillor.\n\nIf you share my vision for restoring common sense to local politics, I invite you to join us. Please email me at chair.nul@reformuk.com, and together, we can begin to make a real difference for our community.","bd":"1969"},{"n":"Elaine Blake","p":"Labour Party","v":249,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128576"},{"n":"Kerri Louise Jackman","p":"Green Party","v":241,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"128579"},{"n":"Steve French","p":"Green Party","v":237,"r":7,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"128578"},{"n":"Moonoon Moontaha Jawadin","p":"Labour Party","v":173,"r":8,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"128580"}],"female_count":5,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":2},{"ward":"Maer & Whitmore","seats":1,"turnout_pct":49.96,"results_url":"https://www.newcastle-staffs.gov.uk/downloads/file/3906/maer-whitmore","candidates":[{"n":"Jeremy John Elton Lefroy","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":562,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"2877","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/125443/d911b21a-acf7-433b-9297-82f988e8d1ae.png","tw":"\"JeremyLefroy\"","bd":"1959"},{"n":"Richard Woodward","p":"Reform UK","v":428,"r":2,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127985"},{"n":"Dave Lee","p":"Labour Party","v":132,"r":3,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"13818","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/13818/52915e27-9fb5-4922-8395-239027068630.png","stmt":"I am proud to be standing again in my home ward. I have lived in the area almost all my life, and to represent Maer & Whitmore would be a great honour.\n\nThere are many challenges to our way of life in this area, and I believe I can best address them from within the Labour Party, the government of the day, using contacts within the party. After many years of Tory chaos, the Labour government is steadying the ship and striving to make people's lives better. But they know it's not one size that fits all. They need to hear what we have to say in Maer, Whitmore and Baldwins Gate. The other candidates (however well-meaning you may think they are) will be just voices in the wilderness, whereas I can reach out to those who are making decisions in our area.\n\nWhether it's housing development, the environment, the state of the roads or local taxes I want to hear YOUR views, not impose mine, in the same way that our new MP Leigh Ingham is doing. So please, give this local candidate a chance so your voices can be heard."}],"female_count":0,"male_count":3,"unknown_count":0,"inc_total":0,"inc_elected":0,"inc_defeated":0,"new_elected":1},{"ward":"May Bank","seats":3,"turnout_pct":41.57,"results_url":"https://www.newcastle-staffs.gov.uk/downloads/file/3915/may-bank","candidates":[{"n":"John Henry Tagg","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":948,"r":1,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"37379"},{"n":"David Hutchison","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":928,"r":2,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","inc":true,"pid":"90343"},{"n":"Finn Swain","p":"Conservative and Unionist Party","v":834,"r":3,"e":true,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"low","pid":"127995"},{"n":"Jackie Olszewski","p":"Labour Party","v":812,"r":4,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"claude","cf":"medium","pid":"127992"},{"n":"Deborah Elizabeth Bailey","p":"Reform UK","v":721,"r":5,"e":false,"g":"female","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127989"},{"n":"Bayley Dickin","p":"Labour Party","v":714,"r":6,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"120312","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127990/aa06441c-453c-42df-b539-303fa43a33bf.png","bd":"2003"},{"n":"Anthony-Claret Ifeanyi Onwutalobi","p":"Labour Party","v":702,"r":7,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"existing","cf":"high","pid":"127993","img":"https://candidates.democracyclub.org.uk/media/images/people/127993/aa02a11e-ddce-4757-973f-039ac3aa1b21.png","stmt":"Maybank is a community defined by resilience, hard work, and a shared pride in where we live. But pride alone is not enough—we must match it with action.\n\nToo many of the everyday issues that matter most to residents still need urgent attention: cleaner streets, safer roads, well-maintained parks, and a stronger, louder voice for our community.\n\nThat is why I am standing.\nNot just to represent — but to deliver.\n\nMy priorities for Maybank:\n✔ Tackling fly-tipping and restoring pride in our streets\n✔ Improving road safety and addressing parking challenges\n✔ Protecting and enhancing our parks and green spaces\n✔ Ensuring every resident is heard, respected, and represented\n✔ Supporting families and championing both younger and older generations\nWhy support Hon. Anthony-Claret Onwutalobi?\n\nRepresentation should be more than a title — it should be a responsibility.\n\nI am deeply committed to this community. I will:\n\nListen without bias\nAct with integrity\nWork tirelessly to deliver real change\n\nI will be present, accessible, and accountable — every single day."},{"n":"Craig Anthony Rolinson","p":"Reform UK","v":675,"r":8,"e":false,"g":"male","m":"gender_guesser","cf":"high","pid":"127